	  <div class="panel-heading">
		<h3 class="panel-title">How it works</h3>
	  </div>
	  <div class="panel-body">
		<p>Use the search bar to search for a monster. Suggestions from the community will appear on the left column.</p>
		<ol> 
		<li>Suggested Subs - These are the subs that are recommended to use with the monster you have searched</li>
		<li>Leader/Leader Pairing - These are the leaders that are recommended to pair with if the monster you have selected will be the leader.</li>
		<li>Ratings as Sub - These ratings here indicate the synergy of the monster you selected with the listed leader.</li>
		</ol>
		<p>The bolded numbers indicate the weighted average for the indicated monster. The number in parenthesis displays the vote counts for the weighted average</p>
		<ol>
		<li>1 to 10 rating scale</li>
		<li>Users may submit a new vote for same pairings once a month</li>
		<li>You may update/correct your existing rating until the next month is up.</li>
		<li>Weighted average ratings are to keep up with the meta. The older the rating, the less it is worth compared to the newer ratings.</li>
		</ol>
		<br>
		<p>New suggestions can be made in the panels in the right column. Use Subs button to add to Suggested Subs, and Leader/Leader button to add to Leader/Leader Pairing.</p>
		<br>
		<p>Tags can be added to the monster which allows the monster to be searched by a particular tag</p>
		<br>
		<p>Click the ratings above a suggested monster icon to bring up a detailed ratings page as well as graphs that represents this monster's rating history.</p>
		<p>Specific pairing tags can be added here to show why the select monster works well in the pair (for example, delay, board changer)</p>
		<p>Comments can be left about the particular pairing.</p>
	  </div>
